.TH STOPHAMMER-RESOLVERCTL 1 "2026-03-19" "stophammer" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
stophammer-resolverctl \- inspect or toggle resolver queue state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B stophammer-resolverctl
[
.BI --db " PATH"
]
[
.B status
|
.B import-active
|
.B import-idle
|
.B re-resolve
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B stophammer-resolverctl
is a small operational helper for the durable resolver queue.

It can:

- print queue counts, import/backfill pause state, and pending review counts
- set
.BR resolver_state.import_active=true
before a large import
- clear that flag afterwards so
.BR stophammer-resolverd
can resume draining the queue
- wipe all resolved state and re-queue every feed for re-resolution
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --db " PATH"
Path to the SQLite database. Defaults to
.BR ./stophammer.db .
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Prints
.BR import_active ,
.BR import_stale ,
.BR import_heartbeat_at ,
.BR backfill_active ,
.BR backfill_stale ,
.BR backfill_heartbeat_at ,
queue total, ready, locked, and failed counts, and pending
.B review_artist_identity_pending
and
.B review_wallet_pending
counts.
.TP
.B import-active
Sets
.BR resolver_state.import_active=true
and refreshes the import heartbeat timestamp.
.TP
.B import-idle
Sets
.BR resolver_state.import_active=false .
.TP
.B re-resolve
Wipes all resolved state and re-queues every feed for re-resolution. Use
with caution: this discards all canonical derived state and forces a full
re-run of the resolver across every feed in the database.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Check queue status:
.nf
cargo run --bin stophammer-resolverctl -- status
.fi
.TP
Pause the queue around a bulk import:
.nf
cargo run --bin stophammer-resolverctl -- import-active
# run bulk import
cargo run --bin stophammer-resolverctl -- import-idle
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR stophammer-resolverd (1),
.BR backfill_canonical (1),
.BR stophammer (1)
